    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "I think this is enough for when.then.otherwise and they should get the idea.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Expression Expansion Idea\n",
        "\n",
        "### Idea 1\n",
        "Many of the columns contain minutes delayed for a particular reason, or the total minutes delayed. Use expression expansion to convert all the columns from minutes to hours by dividing their values by 60. \n",
        "\n",
        "The problem with all these solutions is that the column still says \"minutes\". "
      ],
      "id": "f46b6494"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#long way\n",
        "q3 = q2.with_columns((pl.col('minutes_delayed_carrier',\n",
        "                       'minutes_delayed_late_aircraft',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_nas',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_security',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_weather',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_total') / 60).round(2) )\n",
        "q3"
      ],
      "id": "a7e93d76",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#short way with regex\n",
        "q2.select(\n",
        "    (pl.col(\"^minutes_.*$\") / 60).round(2)\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "70afd5bd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#short way with polars selectors\n",
        "import polars.selectors as cs\n",
        "\n",
        "q2.select(\n",
        "    (cs.starts_with(\"minutes\") / 60).round(2)\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "034453b6",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#fix the column name problem of minutes to hours\n",
        "# this seems a bit too complicated\n",
        "import polars.selectors as cs\n",
        "\n",
        "q2.with_columns([\n",
        "    (pl.col(col) / 60).alias(col.replace(\"minutes\", \"hours\"))\n",
        "    for col in q2.select(cs.starts_with(\"minutes\")).columns  \n",
        "]\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "6631eaa1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Idea 2\n",
        "\n",
        "Maybe just convert all the num_of_delays columns to be in hundreds (i.e. divide them all by 100). __NOTE: If we did this idea, I think we should do this before calculating the new \"weather delays\" column.__\n",
        "\n",
        "But the num_of_delays_carrier is a string, so we have to convert it first. Is that too much too soon? (I don't think so, since they do casting in CSE110 a few times). Maybe we would have to give them a hint, but I think having them figure it out on their own is a good idea, if we cover a similar issue in class. For the online section though a hint may be necessary.\n",
        "\n",
        " I guess we could have them just convert the column 3 columns that will be used for future calculations, but that misses the opportunity to show them these other short cuts for selecting multiple columns.\n",
        "\n",
        "Any other ideas??!\n",
        "\n",
        "#long way\n",
        "q3= q2.filter(pl.col('num_of_delays_carrier') != \"1500+\").with_columns(pl.col('num_of_delays_carrier').cast(int))\n",
        "\n",
        "q3.with_columns((pl.col('num_of_delays_carrier',\n",
        "                       'minutes_delayed_late_aircraft',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_nas',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_security',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_weather',\n",
        "                        'minutes_delayed_total') / 100) )\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#short way with regex\n",
        "df.with_columns(pl.col('num_of_delays_carrier').cast(int)).select(\n",
        "    (pl.col(\"^num_of_delays_.*$\") / 100)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "#short way with polars selectors\n",
        "import polars.selectors as cs\n",
        "\n",
        "q3.select(\n",
        "    (cs.starts_with(\"num_of_delays\") / 100)\n",
        ")\n",
        "# ```"
      ],
      "id": "70c9ccba"
    }
